This program takes a Primer (genome sequence) and finds all matches in the CUR and ORA assemblies that have at most N (user-defined value) mismatches. The path to assemblies are hard coded, but can be changed in check_primer_uniqueness.py.

Run Command:
python3.8 check_primer_uniqueness.py -n 8 -o 1_R_primer.out CAACCTAAAGATAATCAGTGGACATCGG 4

#usage: check_primer_uniqueness.py [-h] [-o O] [-n N] primer maxmm

#positional arguments:
#  primer      Primer sequence to check
#  maxmm       Maximum allowed mismatches

#optional arguments:
#  -h, --help  show this help message and exit
#  -o O        Output file name (default: None)
#  -n N        number of cores to use (default: 1)
